with her, your mother.

14:55.352 --> 14:56.312
Be kind.

14:58.480 --> 14:59.857
We're family again, right?

15:16.290 --> 15:18.042
I love you, Dad.

15:22.004 --> 15:23.297
I love you too.

15:32.848 --> 15:35.476
(MUSIC SWELLS)

15:51.325 --> 15:54.868
Don't say anything,
I'll handle this.

15:54.870 --> 15:57.329
I saw your car,
thought I'd say hi.

15:57.331 --> 15:59.581
- Just out for a walk.
- It's nice day for it.

15:59.583 --> 16:00.874
Who's this?

16:00.876 --> 16:02.503
Not in the mood, Harper.

16:04.380 --> 16:05.506
Hank, what's going on?

16:06.423 --> 16:08.926
Harper, this is Donovan.

16:10.219 --> 16:12.928
Police found him,
called us last night.

16:12.930 --> 16:14.930
Why didn't you tell me?

16:14.932 --> 16:17.557
He's only been
home for a few hours.

16:17.559 --> 16:19.687
Donovan, do you remember me?

16:23.107 --> 16:24.191
Can I come in?

16:26.110 --> 16:27.194
I'm sorry, no.

16:28.278 --> 16:29.113
Not yet.

16:30.531 --> 16:31.446
Linda wouldn't like it.

16:31.448 --> 16:32.948
I have a right to be there.

16:32.950 --> 16:33.909
No, you don't.

16:35.035 --> 16:37.369
Look, I'll talk to her.

16:37.371 --> 16:39.039
Promise me this
stays between us.

16:40.457 --> 16:41.873
This is ridiculous.

16:41.875 --> 16:44.376
Donovan Reid comes
back from the dead.

16:44.378 --> 16:46.420
You can't keep a secret
like that forever.

16:46.422 --> 16:48.088
Not For me, Harper, for him.

16:48.090 --> 16:49.049
Just...

16:52.302 --> 16:53.137
I promise.

16:54.888 --> 16:55.764
I'll see you soon.

17:15.242 --> 17:19.286
Donovan, I need
you upstairs bud.

17:19.288 --> 17:20.497
Someone here to see you.

17:27.087 --> 17:28.420
Good to see you
again, Donovan.

17:28.422 --> 17:29.921
Please take a seat.

17:29.923 --> 17:30.758
Take a seat.

17:36.013 --> 17:39.433
I see you're still playing the
strong and silent type, huh?

17:42.644 --> 17:45.439
- He's barely said a word.
- Hank, I need him to answer.

17:50.027 --> 17:50.861
Verbally.

17:52.112 --> 17:53.864
I need to hear you
speak. Yes or no.

17:55.616 --> 17:56.283
No.

17:56.742 --> 17:57.657
It's a little soon
for this kind of inter...

17:57.659 --> 18:00.160
Memory is subjective, Hank.

18:00.162 --> 18:03.872
Alright? Easily twisted
and misconstrued.

18:03.874 --> 18:08.629
Sometimes because of
trauma, often on purpose.

18:14.468 --> 18:18.386
This is Detective
Schleicher, badge 529

18:18.388 --> 18:22.810
interviewing matching missing
persons case, number 00812.

18:24.895 --> 18:27.314
Can you state your full
name for me please?

18:30.651 --> 18:34.402
Look, if I were in your shoes,

18:34.404 --> 18:37.322
I wouldn't wanna talk
either, I get it.

18:37.324 --> 18:39.993
But I wanna catch the person
who did this, don't you?

18:43.747 --> 18:46.250
Can you state your full
name for me please?

18:51.088 --> 18:54.424
- Donovan Reid.
- And your middle.

19:00.347 --> 19:01.429
- It's...
- No, no, no, no.

19:01.431 --> 19:02.514
Hank I have a right here.

19:02.516 --> 19:03.431
He was only 10.

19:03.433 --> 19:04.432
