19:04.434 --> 19:05.517
every little thing from before.

19:05.519 --> 19:07.102
Yes, I can.

19:07.104 --> 19:09.855
Fourth grade, cursive.

19:09.857 --> 19:12.023
I wrote my name
down so many times,

19:12.025 --> 19:13.861
my hand practically fell off.

19:16.864 --> 19:20.117
Now, did you run away?

19:22.202 --> 19:23.036
No.

19:25.372 --> 19:26.623
Oh, were you taken?

19:29.877 --> 19:30.711
Yes.

19:31.962 --> 19:34.214
SCHLEICHER: How many
people were involved?

19:34.756 --> 19:35.799
One?

19:36.550 --> 19:37.718
Two, three?

19:39.219 --> 19:40.969
One.

19:40.971 --> 19:43.638
- Male or female?
- Female.

19:43.640 --> 19:45.934
- Race.
- White.

19:48.395 --> 19:54.816
SCHLEICHER: Tall, short,
fat, skinny, glasses,

19:54.818 --> 19:57.487
tattoo of a heart on the
back of the neck, details.

19:59.823 --> 20:04.745
Short, no hearts, no glasses.

20:05.579 --> 20:07.915
10 years is a long
time to go missing.

20:09.791 --> 20:10.792
Where have you been?

20:16.673 --> 20:19.468
- A house.
- Where was this house?

20:22.596 --> 20:24.431
What color was the house?

20:27.309 --> 20:28.143
Brown.

20:29.603 --> 20:31.855
SCHLEICHER: And were are
you allowed to go outside?

20:33.941 --> 20:35.275
No.

20:38.862 --> 20:40.946
I'm looking for
Raymond Rakubian.

20:40.948 --> 20:42.322
Don't get cute.

20:42.324 --> 20:44.824
I'm just itching
to work you over.

20:44.826 --> 20:46.954
Soft in the belly,
can't take it.

20:48.372 --> 20:51.291
See, what'd I tell you?

21:01.301 --> 21:03.134
Can't do that to Chester.

21:03.136 --> 21:04.552
I'm gonna blow your guts out.

21:04.554 --> 21:06.682
- Easy.
- Lay off, Chester. Not now.

21:08.225 --> 21:09.226
ELLEN: Michael?

21:10.227 --> 21:11.478
Look at him.

21:11.603 --> 21:13.063
- He's so scared of Chester, he'll talk now
- Michael

21:14.231 --> 21:16.024
- He's not afraid, Chester.
- Michael.

21:18.193 --> 21:21.194
MAN: You can tell from
a man's eyes when he is afraid.

21:21.196 --> 21:26.700
I need you to go to your
room and lock your door

21:26.702 --> 21:33.375
and shut your windows and
be quiet for an hour or two.

21:35.502 --> 21:36.670
Can you do that for me?

21:44.720 --> 21:48.763
So we have a single
white female, short,

21:48.765 --> 21:50.432
no distinguishing features.

21:50.434 --> 21:52.769
I think we ought to start
arresting soccer moms.

21:53.020 --> 21:54.021
Heh.

21:56.023 --> 21:59.024
Hank, I would like to
talk to Donovan alone

21:59.026 --> 22:00.108
if you don't mind.

22:00.110 --> 22:01.028
Absolutely not.

22:01.403 --> 22:04.237
Hank, there are some things
a child would never admit to

22:04.239 --> 22:05.697
in front of a parent, okay?

22:05.699 --> 22:07.117
It's only gonna take a minute.

22:25.969 --> 22:27.469
You're lying.

22:27.471 --> 22:28.430
You're a liar.

22:30.974 --> 22:32.559
Sure, I get it, we all do it.

22:34.561 --> 22:36.229
Only this time it's a felony.

22:41.735 --> 22:42.986
You're a leech.

22:44.488 --> 22:46.446
Attach yourself to people,

22:46.448 --> 22:48.740
people who were hanging
on to some shred of hope

22:48.742 --> 22:50.744
and then you drain
the life out of them?

22:51.578 --> 22:53.330
What kind of a person does that?

22:57.751 --> 22:59.753
I'm coming for you,

23:01.296 --> 23:02.297
"Donovan."

23:13.934 --> 23:17.143
LINDA: That's not
why I called you.

23:17.145 --> 23:18.855
If he's acting, he's good.

23:20.148 --> 23:22.023
You're not here
for your opinions.

23:22.025 --> 23:23.024
I want answers.

23:23.026 --> 23:24.651
It's going to take...

23:24.653 --> 23:27.614
Time. No, no, not an option.

23:29.449 --> 23:31.118
Have you considered
a DNA test?

23:32.494 --> 23:33.495
I...

23:35.622 --> 23:38.500
May I walk you to your car?

23:56.560 --> 23:58.643
I'm having company
over again tonight,

23:58.645 --> 24:01.064
so I'll need you to
stay in your room, okay?

24:08.488 --> 24:09.698
You should eat.

24:11.324 --> 24:12.742
HANK: You should eat.

24:20.167 --> 24:21.916
Sorry if the
vegetarian lifestyle

24:21.918 --> 24:24.169
isn't something you're used to.

24:24.171 --> 24:25.005
It's fine.

24:28.508 --> 24:29.718
Good to hear you talk.

24:31.011 --> 24:32.512
You've already come a long way.

24:33.388 --> 24:34.431
I'm proud of you.

24:36.850 --> 24:38.393
Are you sure you're not hungry?

24:40.937 --> 24:42.564
I'm fine.

24:57.037 --> 24:59.581
Donovan, I haven't been fair.

25:01.458 --> 25:03.875
I've been very
distant, very quiet.

25:03.877 --> 25:04.920
I'm really sorry.

25:06.087 --> 25:08.715
It's good to have you home.

25:11.801 --> 25:14.888
(TENSE MUSIC RISES)

26:18.702 --> 26:22.372
You made a lot of
progress today and your mom,

26:25.333 --> 26:26.710
I think we're gonna make it.

26:46.229 --> 26:49.524
(TENSE DRAMATIC MUSIC)

27:18.762 --> 27:21.846
What happened to you?

27:21.848 --> 27:23.433
What really happened?

27:35.612 --> 27:37.528
Who is this?

27:37.530 --> 27:38.531
(DOOR KNOCKING)

27:44.287 --> 27:46.081
What's all this?

27:50.460 --> 27:51.544
Memories.

28:02.263 --> 28:04.307
May I borrow that?

28:19.072 --> 28:22.409
Would it be alright
if I hugged you?

28:58.862 --> 29:00.113
Thank you.

29:02.198 --> 29:03.700
Good night.

29:10.498 --> 29:13.124
RECORDING: I shouldn't be
talking to you directly.

29:13.126 --> 29:16.169
I'm supposed to report
this kind of thing.

29:16.171 --> 29:20.508
I think you should hear
what Donovan was telling me.

29:21.634 --> 29:25.472
(SOBBING)

29:33.688 --> 29:36.481
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

29:36.483 --> 29:38.985
(TENSE MUSIC)

30:49.806 --> 30:52.475
(DOOR SHUTTING)

30:59.148 --> 31:01.776
(DOOR KNOCKING)

31:10.159 --> 31:12.245
- Hey.
- Hey.

31:13.413 --> 31:16.499
- He can talk.
- Yeah.

31:18.751 --> 31:20.587
Can I come in
just for a minute?

31:22.422 --> 31:25.008
- Dad wouldn't...
- Yeah, I know.

31:26.342 --> 31:28.759
How are you with everything?

31:28.761 --> 31:30.763
I don't even know what to ask.

31:32.599 --> 31:34.432
I'm okay.

31:34.434 --> 31:37.937
I just wanted to see
you and give you this.

31:41.357 --> 31:42.940
It's about you.

31:42.942 --> 31:45.612
So I figured I should be the
one to tell you about it.

31:46.821 --> 31:48.029
I'm gonna to talk to Hank

31:48.031 --> 31:49.949
and see if we can spend
some time together.

31:51.367 --> 31:52.785
Maybe I'll see you tomorrow?

31:56.789 --> 31:58.333
Okay, good night.

32:02.712 --> 32:05.798
(EMOTIONAL PIANO MUSIC)

32:49.759 --> 32:52.510
This is the last
time for a while.

32:52.512 --> 32:55.098
I just need you to keep
quiet in here, okay?

32:57.392 --> 32:58.518
I'll see you in a bit.

33:05.191 --> 33:07.694
(DRAMATIC PIANO MUSIC RISES)

34:18.764 --> 34:21.139
Hey! Do you like 'em?

34:21.141 --> 34:23.516
Wasn't really sure
on the size since,

34:23.518 --> 34:26.478
well, you've grown.
But I wanted to make sure

34:26.481 --> 34:29.815
you had something new,
something that's yours.

34:29.817 --> 34:30.985
We can always get more.

34:32.779 --> 34:35.822
Before I forget, I've got
something else for you.

34:37.449 --> 34:40.828
Not only has calling for
now, but if you ever need us.

34:44.706 --> 34:47.376
So Harper was here, huh?

34:48.710 --> 34:52.047
I saw the book, her book.

35:00.389 --> 35:04.058
Look, I need
you to be careful.

35:04.060 --> 35:05.978
Just keep it hidden.

35:07.230 --> 35:08.813
I just wanna remember.

35:08.815 --> 35:09.982
We all do.

35:11.025 --> 35:15.655
It's just, it's the reason
your mom kicked Harper out.

35:17.323 --> 35:20.743
- Harper was...
- Here, yeah, two years.

35:23.412 --> 35:24.705
It's not my story to tell.

35:26.082 --> 35:31.087
It got contentious between them.

35:31.671 --> 35:34.090
Your mom asked me
to keep Harper away.

35:37.552 --> 35:39.009
(DOOR KNOCKING)

35:39.011 --> 35:39.846
I'll get it.

35:51.607 --> 35:53.357
(YELLING)

35:53.359 --> 35:55.401
SCHLEICHER: I wanted to
check back in with Donovan

35:55.403 --> 35:56.902
I've already spoken to Linda.

35:56.904 --> 35:58.362
HANK: Well then you'd be
come back when she's home.

35:58.364 --> 36:00.072
SCHLEICHER: Look everything
is gonna go a lot easier

36:00.074 --> 36:03.742
if I have your full
cooperation, Hank, for Donovan.

36:03.744 --> 36:05.286
HANK: Look,
just keep it quick.

36:05.288 --> 36:07.204
Hey, you'll hardly
know I was here.

36:07.206 --> 36:08.455
How are you doing Donovan?

36:08.457 --> 36:10.457
Can I talk to you
for a few minutes?

36:10.459 --> 36:15.464
New look, new family, new life.

36:17.925 --> 36:19.051
You seem pretty well.

36:19.886 --> 36:21.552
I'm all right, thanks.

36:21.554 --> 36:24.972
Okay, well I'd like to pick
up where we left off, alright?

36:24.974 --> 36:28.475
We'll keep it simple,
although I would appreciate it

36:28.477 --> 36:31.439
if you gave me more than just
one word answers this time

36:32.273 --> 36:34.231
- I can do that.
- Okay.

36:34.233 --> 36:37.067
Now, the day that you were
taken, you mentioned a woman.

36:37.069 --> 36:39.570
Short, white skin.

36:39.572 --> 36:40.990
Anything else you wanna add?

36:44.118 --> 36:47.328
- It wasn't a woman.
- Really?

36:47.330 --> 36:48.164
I lied.

36:49.165 --> 36:50.748
It was a man.

36:50.750 --> 36:51.751
Tell me about him.

36:55.338 --> 36:59.926
He had dark hair, a dimple,

37:01.761 --> 37:05.512
- real tall.
- Tall, dark hair, dimple.

37:05.514 --> 37:06.349
Anything else?

37:07.767 --> 37:10.353
He had a nice suit on.

37:12.855 --> 37:13.812
He had a gun.

37:13.814 --> 37:15.024
A nice suit and a gun.

37:16.359 --> 37:18.027
Okay, would you
like to add to that?

37:20.780 --> 37:23.364
- No.
- Come on, he was just a kid.

37:23.366 --> 37:24.325
I was scared.

37:25.451 --> 37:27.534
But you're safe now, right?

37:27.536 --> 37:28.955
I mean, don't you feel safe?

37:30.790 --> 37:33.125
The kidnapping,
walk me through it.

37:34.377 --> 37:35.542
What?

37:35.544 --> 37:36.796
The kidnapping
where were you?

37:42.218 --> 37:43.511
The beach.

37:47.890 --> 37:50.977
Okay, would you like to
elaborate on that further?

37:51.978 --> 37:56.480
I can't remember.

37:56.482 --> 38:00.361
But you are sure you were
taken at the beach, right?

38:01.696 --> 38:04.238
I think so.

38:04.240 --> 38:09.036
Okay, because I have your
mother stating on record

38:10.162 --> 38:12.329
that you were
taken at the house.

38:12.331 --> 38:14.873
Now you lied to me
about who took you

38:14.875 --> 38:17.084
and now you're lying to me
about where they took you.

38:17.086 --> 38:20.339
- I ran away.
- Excuse me.

38:21.841 --> 38:24.510
I ran away to the beach.

38:25.678 --> 38:26.885
That's where the man took me.

38:26.887 --> 38:28.055
Enough!

38:29.223 --> 38:30.264
Now Look, you've
got a description.

38:30.266 --> 38:31.684
Leave us alone.

38:32.518 --> 38:34.020
Go find who did this.

38:37.732 --> 38:38.733
(RECORDER BEEPS)

38:42.611 --> 38:44.572
It shouldn't be long now.

38:51.954 --> 38:53.620
HANK: He had no right.

38:53.622 --> 38:55.414
- I should have...
- It's fine.

38:55.416 --> 38:56.248
It's fine.

38:56.250 --> 38:57.084
I'm okay.

38:57.918 --> 39:01.422
Look, I'll sort
it out with Linda.

39:04.091 --> 39:05.801
I wanna go to my room.

39:06.802 --> 39:11.265
Oh, I thought we'd
go do something fun.

39:15.895 --> 39:16.729
Maybe later.

39:40.920 --> 39:43.589
(DOOR KNOCKING)

39:52.139 --> 39:53.432
How you holding up?

39:55.017 --> 39:56.644
- I'm good.
- Good.

39:57.686 --> 40:00.437
- Your parents?
- They're doing better.

40:00.439 --> 40:02.358
Good, great even.

40:04.527 --> 40:06.612
You packing or what?

40:08.864 --> 40:12.368
Just trying to remember.

40:13.994 --> 40:14.829
You read it?

40:16.372 --> 40:18.791
- How much?
- All of it.

40:21.293 --> 40:23.712
I guess you probably
have some questions then.

40:24.463 --> 40:25.297
A few.

40:26.632 --> 40:29.135
Hey, you wanna go somewhere?

40:33.973 --> 40:36.642
(DOOR SHUTTING)

40:39.645 --> 40:40.646
(DISTANT OCEAN)

40:55.161 --> 40:57.995
(LAUGHING)

40:57.997 --> 40:59.246
I don't know if you remember,

40:59.248 --> 41:01.667
but we used to hang
out here all the time.

41:03.002 --> 41:05.504
I still come here when
I'm feeling shitty.

41:07.673 --> 41:10.716
I'm really happy
you're doing well.

41:10.718 --> 41:11.552
You said that.

41:13.596 --> 41:15.431
So the book,

41:16.891 --> 41:21.602
I was trying to tell an old
story with a new perspective.

41:21.604 --> 41:24.271
It's just, no one
really talks about

41:24.273 --> 41:25.858
the people that get left behind.

41:28.194 --> 41:30.110
Did I leave you behind?

41:30.112 --> 41:32.615
No! Well, not exactly.

41:34.408 --> 41:37.117
When someone dies
or goes missing,

41:37.119 --> 41:38.368
the people who are close to them

41:38.370 --> 41:41.874
just have to continue
on, you know?

41:45.586 --> 41:47.794
I wish I could have been here.

41:47.796 --> 41:50.547
That's sweet but you read it.

41:50.549 --> 41:54.053
It was just an example
of dealing with grief.

41:54.929 --> 41:56.303
Try not to roll your eyes.

41:56.305 --> 42:00.265
It was just a way to
process everything.

42:00.267 --> 42:01.477
Narrative therapy.

42:03.437 --> 42:08.150
- But Mom didn't like it.
- No, not even a little bit.

42:10.778 --> 42:12.819
I moved out when I was 16

42:12.821 --> 42:15.324
and Hank let me stay at
the house for a while.

42:16.450 --> 42:19.453
The book ruined everything.

42:20.579 --> 42:21.664
She was furious.

42:23.249 --> 42:24.915
- I'm sorry.
- Nah.

42:24.917 --> 42:27.169
It's how I got my job
at the Coastal Weekly.

42:29.505 --> 42:31.340
How are your parents
handling it all?

42:34.468 --> 42:35.970
Dad's doing better than Mom.

42:37.012 --> 42:38.472
That's not a surprise.

42:42.977 --> 42:44.520
Have you told anyone?

42:47.106 --> 42:50.691
The whole town went looking
for you when you disappeared.

42:50.693 --> 42:53.527
They'd wanna know you survived.

42:53.529 --> 42:55.823
It'd be like closure.

42:57.199 --> 42:59.032
I could write a story.

42:59.034 --> 43:02.454
Dad says I shouldn't
tell anybody.

43:03.289 --> 43:05.541
Didn't want you to
hang out with me either.

43:10.212 --> 43:12.504
- All right.
- Cool.

43:12.506 --> 43:15.384
I can probably have something
printed for tomorrow.

43:18.554 --> 43:23.223
- So what do I do now?
- I'll handle it.

43:23.225 --> 43:24.226
Don't worry.

43:25.227 --> 43:28.314
(TENSE PIANO MUSIC)

44:02.848 --> 44:05.517
(WATER FLOWING)

45:26.640 --> 45:29.184
(SOFT PIANO MUSIC)

46:22.654 --> 46:25.365
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

46:38.420 --> 46:41.882
(TENSE MUSIC RISES)

46:49.223 --> 46:50.599
Dad?

46:53.685 --> 46:54.895
Donovan.

47:02.903 --> 47:04.446
Where were you?

47:06.198 --> 47:07.616
Where were you!

47:09.743 --> 47:10.951
With Harper.

47:10.953 --> 47:11.954
Oh.

47:13.205 --> 47:14.623
With Harper.

47:19.628 --> 47:22.963
I told you and her,

47:22.965 --> 47:24.800
you can't just run
away like that.

47:28.220 --> 47:29.596
I just wanted to see her.

47:30.597 --> 47:31.807
So you disappear on me?

47:32.266 --> 47:33.267
Hm?

47:34.101 --> 47:34.935
No.

47:35.811 --> 47:37.938
Think about what was
going on in my head.

47:39.439 --> 47:44.236
My son, who's been missing
for a decade, just disappears.

47:46.238 --> 47:47.239
I'm sorry.

47:49.741 --> 47:50.742
Maybe it's me.

47:52.411 --> 47:55.414
You're an adult now and I'm
still treating you like a kid.

47:57.416 --> 47:58.915
You can make your own decisions,

47:58.917 --> 48:02.754
but I'm just trying to
do what's best for you.

48:04.423 --> 48:05.632
I know.

48:07.175 --> 48:08.427
I'm sorry.

48:09.511 --> 48:11.303
(SOBBING)

48:11.305 --> 48:13.932
(SOFT PIANO MUSIC)

48:20.188 --> 48:21.189
Dad...

48:23.108 --> 48:27.821
Can we have breakfast
as a family, tomorrow?

48:29.448 --> 48:31.950
Sure, of course.

48:34.286 --> 48:36.830
I'll talk to your mom
when she gets home.

48:38.665 --> 48:43.211
- And Harper.
- Why?

48:46.048 --> 48:47.299
She's family.

48:51.219 --> 48:52.054
Okay.

48:54.222 --> 48:57.225
I'll see what I can do.

49:25.837 --> 49:28.924
(TENSE PIANO MUSIC)

49:51.071 --> 49:53.238
FEMALE VOICE : Okay, this is
on, right?

49:53.240 --> 49:54.241
Okay, great.

49:55.534 --> 49:57.367
This is Ms. K.

49:57.369 --> 49:59.119
I shouldn't be talking
to you directly.

49:59.121 --> 50:01.371
I'm supposed to report
this kind of thing

50:01.373 --> 50:04.124
but I really think
you should hear

50:04.126 --> 50:06.044
what Donovan's been telling me.

50:06.545 --> 50:10.255
Donovan, can you tell me
what you just said again?

50:10.257 --> 50:11.216
YOUNG DONOVAN: Huh?

50:12.467 --> 50:16.302
You just told me, what was it
that you wanted to tell me?

50:16.304 --> 50:17.137
I don't know.

50:17.139 --> 50:18.722
I'm counting the lights.

50:18.724 --> 50:21.975
MS. K: Donovan,
I need you to focus.

50:21.977 --> 50:25.437
What did you tell
me about the bath?

50:25.439 --> 50:26.980
YOUNG DONOVAN: Oh the bath?

50:26.982 --> 50:29.315
My mum said me she wanted
to push me under the water.

50:29.317 --> 50:30.984
MS. K: Okay and was that it?

50:30.986 --> 50:32.569
YOUNG DONOVAN: She
said she never wanted

50:32.571 --> 50:34.112
to let me back up.

50:34.114 --> 50:36.158
I can hold my breath
for this many.

50:37.325 --> 50:39.576
MS. K: Mrs.
Reid, I understand

50:39.578 --> 50:42.328
that Donovan has an
active imagination

50:42.330 --> 50:44.414
but I don't know how
to react to this.

50:44.416 --> 50:46.291
When you and I are
in a room together,

50:46.293 --> 50:49.127
I can never get him
to say these things.

50:49.129 --> 50:52.756
I'd like you to come in tomorrow
so we can talk about this.

50:52.758 --> 50:57.010
Otherwise, I have to call
Child Protective Services,

50:57.012 --> 50:58.180
I'm sorry.

51:06.438 --> 51:09.524
(DOOR KNOCKING)

51:13.695 --> 51:14.529
Michael.

51:20.994 --> 51:23.830
I'm sorry that it
has to be like this.

51:25.957 --> 51:28.126
I know that it's frustrating.

51:31.797 --> 51:34.216
(TENSE MUSIC)

51:37.886 --> 51:39.054
What did you do?

51:41.890 --> 51:43.807
Where did you go?

51:43.809 --> 51:45.892
I told you never to
leave this house.

51:45.894 --> 51:47.813
I'm trying to protect you.

51:49.815 --> 51:52.148
If I ever catch you
outside this house again,

51:52.150 --> 51:53.817
you won't be welcome back.

51:53.819 --> 51:55.487
Do you understand?

52:08.416 --> 52:09.417
Shit!

52:10.502 --> 52:12.754
What are you doing to me?

52:15.006 --> 52:16.216
You're not Donovan.

52:19.845 --> 52:20.679
This proves it.

52:24.766 --> 52:25.600
Careful.

52:33.108 --> 52:37.193
Now, this test only
takes 24 hours,

52:37.195 --> 52:43.285
so if you're smart, you
won't be here tomorrow.

52:50.876 --> 52:53.962
(MUSIC INTENSIFIES)

53:12.814 --> 53:15.317
(INTENSE MUSIC PEAKS)

53:15.734 --> 53:18.403
(DRILL ROARING)

53:33.627 --> 53:36.338
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

53:50.268 --> 53:53.353
I hope you can forgive me

53:53.355 --> 53:56.524
for taking everything
you left behind.

53:57.525 --> 54:00.111
(WISTFUL MUSIC)

54:42.570 --> 54:45.907
(WATER WAVES SPLASHING)

54:49.577 --> 54:50.412
Hey.

54:52.330 --> 54:53.164
Hey.

54:55.542 --> 54:56.751
What you doing out here?

54:58.503 --> 55:00.169
I shouldn't be here.

55:00.171 --> 55:01.506
I'm thinking about leaving.

55:05.010 --> 55:06.759
I wouldn't blame you.

55:06.761 --> 55:08.594
It's been a hard couple
of days last night,

55:08.596 --> 55:10.557
you saw me at my worst.

55:15.020 --> 55:16.688
Hadn't had a drink
in nine years.

55:18.857 --> 55:20.358
Your mom convinced me to stop.

55:24.904 --> 55:28.533
I keep waiting to see
the son I recognize.

55:33.413 --> 55:36.374
I'm never getting
him back, am I?

55:38.918 --> 55:39.878
I don't know.

55:49.721 --> 55:53.224
Look, if you wanna
leave, you can leave.

55:54.476 --> 55:55.810
I really hope you'll stay.

56:01.900 --> 56:03.983
I love you.

56:03.985 --> 56:04.903
I love you too.

56:06.738 --> 56:09.324
Hey, how about you
stay for breakfast.

56:11.826 --> 56:12.660
Yeah.

56:13.745 --> 56:16.245
- Harper coming?
- Yeah, yeah.

56:16.247 --> 56:17.082
She's excited.

56:19.417 --> 56:20.919
You really like her, don't you?

56:22.128 --> 56:23.920
Yeah.

56:23.922 --> 56:26.089
Well, your mother will just
have to make some compromises

56:26.091 --> 56:27.423
like the rest of us.

56:27.425 --> 56:29.010
Come on, let's get started.

56:47.362 --> 56:50.532
Honey, you almost
ready for breakfast?

56:52.534 --> 56:53.952
Harper will be here soon.

56:55.662 --> 56:56.955
She's coming here?

56:58.706 --> 57:00.625
Your son asked
me to invite her.

57:01.292 --> 57:03.126
We'll I've got work.

57:03.128 --> 57:06.796
Linda, we're blessed
to have our son back.

57:06.798 --> 57:09.465
This morning he told me he
was thinking about leaving.

57:09.467 --> 57:11.302
Hell, I don't blame him.

57:12.345 --> 57:13.555
Oh...

57:14.347 --> 57:16.808
If he's thinking
of running away,

57:18.143 --> 57:20.812
maybe a good family breakfast
is just what we need.

57:21.479 --> 57:24.689
With Harper?
(DOOR KNOCKS)

57:24.691 --> 57:27.152
- Sure.
- Thank you.

57:28.319 --> 57:30.155
That saves me one
awkward conversation.

57:36.327 --> 57:40.079
I drove three hours last
night to drop that sample off.

57:40.081 --> 57:42.667
The results will be back
as early as this afternoon.

57:46.546 --> 57:48.214
You still have a few hours.

58:21.748 --> 58:24.584
I'll be out back,
don't go anywhere, okay?

58:25.752 --> 58:28.211
- I wanna go.
- You can't.

58:28.213 --> 58:32.300
- I already told you.
- I wanna go outside.

58:34.636 --> 58:37.136
Don't make this
more difficult.

58:37.138 --> 58:37.972
Please.

58:55.740 --> 58:57.406
Not in a million
years did I think

58:57.408 --> 58:59.575
I'd be sitting here with
all of you like this.

58:59.577 --> 59:02.997
It's like a dream,
like you never left.

59:05.792 --> 59:07.126
Your mother feels the same.

59:10.296 --> 59:16.594
It's been hard, hasn't it Linda?

59:19.264 --> 59:23.474
Yes, yes. Donovan,

59:23.476 --> 59:27.188
When you went missing,
everyone wanted to help

59:28.481 --> 59:30.356
and hours, days, weeks passed

59:30.358 --> 59:31.859
nobody wanted to help then.

59:32.860 --> 59:34.694
Our families disappeared.

59:34.696 --> 59:37.782
Reporters were sucking
stories out of us.

59:38.866 --> 59:42.203
Trust, God trust.

59:44.289 --> 59:47.208
A foreign concept
in a distant land.

59:53.339 --> 59:55.798
But now we have our son back.

59:55.800 --> 59:57.010
Thank you, Donovan,

59:57.885 --> 01:00:01.889
for being the one person
this family can trust.

01:00:03.891 --> 01:00:05.977
Thank you, Linda.

01:00:06.519 --> 01:00:07.520
Mmmm

01:00:08.563 --> 01:00:11.314
Why are you here?

01:00:11.316 --> 01:00:13.065
For him, obviously.

01:00:13.067 --> 01:00:14.984
- For your career, maybe.
- Excuse me.

01:00:14.986 --> 01:00:15.653
Linda.

01:00:16.154 --> 01:00:17.403
No, she took the hardest
moments of our lives

01:00:17.405 --> 01:00:19.155
and used them to get ahead.

01:00:19.157 --> 01:00:20.573
That book is the only
reason she became

01:00:20.575 --> 01:00:22.408
a sorry excuse for a journalist.

01:00:22.410 --> 01:00:24.493
That book helped
me process my grief.

01:00:24.495 --> 01:00:25.661
You've used us.

01:00:25.663 --> 01:00:27.246
Now look, we're
all here for Donovan.

01:00:27.248 --> 01:00:28.247
Are we?

01:00:28.249 --> 01:00:30.335
- What are you saying?
- Stop!

01:00:39.010 --> 01:00:40.595
Thank you for breakfast honey.

01:00:40.887 --> 01:00:43.014
Please stay, please.

01:00:44.724 --> 01:00:46.432
Your son is here.

01:00:46.434 --> 01:00:48.684
This breakfast is
important to him.

01:00:48.686 --> 01:00:52.190
Well, dinner will be
far more interesting.

01:00:53.107 --> 01:00:54.692
The test results will be ready.

01:00:55.860 --> 01:00:59.111
- What test?
- The DNA test.

01:00:59.113 --> 01:01:02.116
That detective was bothering
me about it, insisting even.

01:01:02.950 --> 01:01:06.118
There's no harm in
knowing for certain.

01:01:06.120 --> 01:01:07.119
His blood, how did you...

01:01:07.121 --> 01:01:08.788
It was just a small sample.

01:01:08.790 --> 01:01:10.039
Donovan didn't give
me any trouble.

01:01:10.041 --> 01:01:10.958
Did you sweetie?

01:01:12.460 --> 01:01:13.751
Linda, we need
to talk about this.

01:01:13.753 --> 01:01:17.882
No, we can celebrate
the good news tonight.

01:01:20.593 --> 01:01:23.638
(FOOTSTEPS STOMPING)

01:01:34.565 --> 01:01:35.940
Your mother knows best.

01:01:35.942 --> 01:01:38.567
So you're okay
with what she did.

01:01:38.569 --> 01:01:41.489
Making him take a DNA test
without talking to you about it.

01:01:42.824 --> 01:01:45.408
People deal with
grief differently.

01:01:45.410 --> 01:01:47.243
You wrote a book on yours.

01:01:47.245 --> 01:01:49.288
That was your way, this is hers.

01:01:49.789 --> 01:01:50.913
LINDA: Hank.

01:01:50.915 --> 01:01:51.916
(FOOTSTEPS STOMPING)

01:01:55.420 --> 01:01:58.421
What the hell is this?

01:01:58.423 --> 01:02:00.840
- Why would you do this?
- Let me explain.

01:02:00.842 --> 01:02:02.135
I gave her permission.

01:02:03.428 --> 01:02:05.469
- It's my life.
- No, it's not.

01:02:05.471 --> 01:02:06.305
Why would you?

01:02:07.098 --> 01:02:07.930
This is not okay.

01:02:07.932 --> 01:02:09.434
Out, now.

01:02:18.943 --> 01:02:22.945
I hope you're
happy, both of you.

01:02:22.947 --> 01:02:24.822
- Linda, we can...
- No, we can talk later.

01:02:24.824 --> 01:02:27.160
We need to deal
with this as a family.

01:02:40.131 --> 01:02:42.800
(PHONE RINGING)

01:02:54.562 --> 01:02:56.061
Hello.

01:02:56.063 --> 01:02:58.314
DARYLL: Hi, this is Daryll
with TruMatch DNA Services.

01:02:58.316 --> 01:03:00.985
I was just calling to let you
know that we've run the test.

01:03:04.071 --> 01:03:05.656
Hello, is someone there?

01:03:07.074 --> 01:03:08.991
This is Hank Reid.

01:03:08.993 --> 01:03:10.409
DARYLL: Just
wanted to let you know

01:03:10.411 --> 01:03:13.329
we'll be emailing you the
results in the next hour or so.

01:03:13.331 --> 01:03:15.875
I'll be sure to give you a
call once we've sent them.

01:03:28.930 --> 01:03:31.766
(WAVES SPLASHING)

01:03:42.860 --> 01:03:43.736
Harper?

01:03:45.112 --> 01:03:46.405
Why are you here?

01:03:48.199 --> 01:03:50.576
- Are you alright?
- No.

01:03:53.704 --> 01:03:55.706
Listen, I can't
stay here anymore.

01:03:56.958 --> 01:04:00.876
- Did they kick you out?
- No.

01:04:00.878 --> 01:04:02.213
Then you should go back.

01:04:03.923 --> 01:04:05.047
It's not safe.

01:04:05.049 --> 01:04:07.132
The world isn't safe, Donovan.

01:04:07.134 --> 01:04:08.719
You know that better than most.

01:04:09.971 --> 01:04:10.972
I can't go back.

01:04:13.432 --> 01:04:16.892
After everything,
you're just gonna run?

01:04:16.894 --> 01:04:21.107
- Come with me.
- Come with you.

01:04:22.233 --> 01:04:24.318
Harper, I love you.

01:04:29.991 --> 01:04:33.075
Linda was talking
about a DNA test.

